# Important constraints

- pgvector uses cosine similarity: always use `<=>` operator.
- Embeddings are always 768 dimensions (`text-embedding-004`).
- Business unit filter is ALWAYS applied to vector search — never search across all BUs without explicit intent.
- Incident and ticket embeddings are in separate tables — never mix.
- Sessions stored in PostgreSQL, NOT Redis (Redis is only for caching).
- JIRA API calls must go through the `jira_fetch` tool only.
- Streaming responses use SSE — FastAPI `StreamingResponse` with `text/event-stream`.
